==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*διά / dia / dee-ah'

===Etymology===
A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through (in very wide applications, local, causal or occasional). In composition it retains the same general import: 

===Preposition===
'''διά'''
# [[through]], [[via]], [[during]]
===Usage Notes===
When the object of διά is in the genitive case, the meaning is generally to be taken in a spatial sense, as in "crossing through a desert."  When it is in accusative, it is meant in a causal sense, as in "victory through perseverance."

